adviseScripts.text: My throat's been really sore lately.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Do you know any tricks to keep your throat in good shape?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Drink a lot of warm water.
Relax your throat before singing.
I actually prefer cold drinks,
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: but as long as it's good for the throat, I can try something different.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Thanks for the tip.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Thanks for the tip, but relaxing too much can actually be detrimental to your throat.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Isn't there any other way?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise and I discuss ways a singer can take care of their throat.
Did you see my comeback show several days ago?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: What'd you think?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Sorry, I was out on a mission.
I'm not so sure about the lighting at the end.
Oh, I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: It's okay, duty calls, after all. I appreciate you being honest.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: You can watch a rerun of it whenever you have time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: The lighting?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: The last song was a ballad. They only used 3 fixed lights the entire time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: ... Did you actually watch the show?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: If you didn't, just say so.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise and I discussed her show.
I'm curious about your taste in music.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Whose songs do you usually listen to?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Your songs.
Aria's songs.
Oh... you listen to my songs more?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I'm touched!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I'll have to put even more effort into my next song.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Oh... so you prefer operas?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: That's a completely different genre, so I don't know much about it. Aria's performances are really beautiful though.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Well, looks like I'll need to work harder to make you listen to my songs more often.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise and I discussed music for a while.
Someone asked me about commercial jingles not long ago.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: To be honest, I know next to nothing about them.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Do you think I could pull it off?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Of course you could.
There's a first time for everything. Just give it your best shot.
Really?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I appreciate your confidence in me, but what makes you so sure?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I don't believe anything in this world is an absolute certainty.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Thank you, Producer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I'll do my best.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I spend some time giving Noise earnest advice.
Hey, check this out.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: What do you think?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise plays a song that sounds eerily familiar to one of her own.
Did someone rip off your song?
Is this a cover of one of your songs?
That's right! It's blatant plagiarism.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Completely unacceptable.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Can you help me take legal action against them?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: More like a note-for-note imitation.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: The only thing different is the title.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: This is plagiarism, plain and simple.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise and I examine the copycat song further.
I've been thinking about writing a song that really represents the Prima Donna group.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Do you think that'd be a good idea?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: You three all have wildly different styles. You'd end up with a discordant mess.
You three all have wildly different styles. You'd end up with a song that's full of twists and turns.
Yeah, that's what I was worried about...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I was just hoping something good might come out of it by chance.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: But now that you've confirmed my suspicions, I'll lay this idea to rest.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: That's exactly what I was thinking!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I'll have to look into this further...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Just imagine, what if it suddenly becomes a smash hit?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise and I discussed group songs for a while.
I wrote a new song.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I want to release it on the day we take back the surface.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I just don't know what the title should be.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Homecoming.
Until That Day Comes.
Short and sweet.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I like it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: That truly will be the day that we come home.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Hmm, I think that title puts a little too much emphasis on waiting.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: It's supposed to be released on the day when it all really comes true.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: How about we call it "That Day"?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise and I discussed song titles as well as our anticipation for the future.
Ugh...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I don't know how many days I've been staying up late to practice.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: You should take a nap.
I'll get you some mint-flavored Splendamin.
You're probably right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I'll just leave for a moment...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Thanks, but no thanks.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I feel bad cutting into our precious discussion time,
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: but could I go sleep for a while?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Since Noise went off to bed, I spent some quiet time by myself.
Producer, can I ask you something?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: My fans are always writing letters to me and sending gifts.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: How should I express my appreciation? What should I do to repay these fans?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Shout "I love you guys!" to them while on stage.
Send gifts back to them.
Are you sure "love" isn't too strong?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Hmm...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I love you guys! Everyone can have a piece of me!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Um... yeah, that's good...
It's a little awkward. I'll think of something else.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: That's a great idea!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: What do you think the fans would like to get?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: How about some of my merch? They'd probably enjoy that, right?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise and I discussed how she could better appreciate her fans.
Doesn't being a part-time producer weigh down on you? You already have your hands full being a Commander.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: You can take a rest if you need to. Don't worry about me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I'm totally fine, really.
I'm a little tired, but it's okay.
You don't look fine to me...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: You can be honest with me if you're tired.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: You don't need to push yourself.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I appreciate you being honest with me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I'll do my best to make it all worth your while.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise and I had a heartfelt conversation.
How would you feel about someone admitting their feelings
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: for you during a concert?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I'd feel happy.
I'd feel awkward.
Yeah, if two people really like each other,
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: it shouldn't matter when or how you announce it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: So... at the concert next month...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I guess you're right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: It should be on an occasion when both sides are ready.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: ... I guess the concert next month isn't the proper time.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise and I discuss different ways to tell someone that you like them.
I appreciate that people are interested in me,
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: but I often have people recording me without asking permission.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: What am I supposed to do in that kind of situation?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Chew them out.
Make a funny face.
... You know I'm not Volume, right?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Volume can do whatever she wants...I envy her sometimes.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Aha! Are you saying I should deliberately sabotage their photo?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: All right, I'll start practicing today.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Can you make a face to me? Show me how to do it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise and I discussed paparazzi for a while longer.
I'm practicing my new signature.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I've been using this current one for a few years now, so I need to switch things up
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: These are the top contenders, could you take a look?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: What if people can't recognize your new signature?
Let me see.
Hmm, that's a good point.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: It'd be unfair to anyone who's gotten an autograph from me in the past.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: All right, I'll go with something a bit more streamlined and recognizable instead.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I've prepared five different examples.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: This one incorporates some stars, this one has musical notes, this one has a mic...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: ... They all look the same to me.
You don't have to say anything. It's written on your face.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise and I had a fun time going out to buy some pens for her new signature.
Someone said one of my songs is a rip-off of theirs!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: What is this, some kind of cruel joke?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I nearly fainted when they told me that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: You've got to believe in yourself.
So...who plagiarized who?
You're right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I only acted that way because I was too self-conscious.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I need to have more faith in myself.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: ... Sorry.
Noise and I discussed the tortuous process of musical creation.
Um... this is embarrassing to admit...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: but... there seem to be pictures of me circling around the internet.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: ... Not entirely wholesome images at that.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Must be a twisted admirer of yours.
You need to report them.
Yes, perhaps they were just expressing their fondness for me, albeit in a perverse fashion.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: But it still makes me feel uncomfortable.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I can't let this sort of thing slide.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: My thoughts exactly.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I've considered it from every angle, and this seems to be the best way of handling it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Thanks for helping me make up my mind.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise and I talked more about cybercrimes.
I have a diehard fan who's supported me ever since I was a busker.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: He's been spending so much money on my limited-edition merchandise, that his financial situation has gotten precarious.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I'm happy that someone likes me so much, but I hate to see their life being negatively impacted because of it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Make some exclusive merch just for him.
He could be perfectly happy living like this.
Wow, that's a great idea!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: If he and I took a photo together, that'd be the ultimate piece of memorabilia for him.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I'm putting it in my schedule now.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I don't know about you,
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: but to me, nothing about that is normal. Taking care of yourself should take priority above anything else.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Sacrificing or compromising your own life so that you can follow someone else's is no way to live.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise shared more memorable fan interactions with me.
Someone knocked off one of my songs, and they're actually making money off of it!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: They had the nerve to say it was one of my unpublished B-sides.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I don't want to say it was someone working for me, but...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: How is that possible?
It's unfortunate, but I think you're right.
I hate to suspect my staff, but it's the only logical explanation.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: In this line of work, these kinds of unfortunate situations are inevitable.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: It just breaks my heart.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: It's hard to let it go.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Being betrayed by someone you know
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: is something you never get used to.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: For a long time, Noise and I quietly looked up at the sky.
Someone told me I should try out a sexy look for once.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: It's not that I lack confidence or anything, I just don't want people gossiping about me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: What do you think, Producer?
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Are you not sexy already?
I don't think it suits you.
... I swear...
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: You don't have to say it like that!
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: You're right. I'm just a frumpy singer-songwriter.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: That's not what I meant...
We're done here.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise and I discussed different looks for singers.
I got an offer from this reality show. They follow you around recording your daily life with next to no editing.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I'll be able to show the audience the real me.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: But I'm still a little hesitant.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Only do it if you're willing to be completely open and honest.
A little mystery can be a good thing.
In that case... I won't do it.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Not everything should be made public.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: ... Such as group photos with others and so on.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Oh, I see.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I'm an entertainer first and foremost.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: It's good if I maintain a slight mystique.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I'd better not go.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise and I discussed popular shows for a while.
If you ask me, I think you're ready for your own debut, Producer.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: You've easy on the eyes, and you're in good shape. You're a little reserved, but that can have its own charm too.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I'm sure you'd have plenty of fans.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I have more important things to do.
I'd end up offending many people, racking up scandals.
Oh, right.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: I almost forgot that you're a commander as well.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Don't you dare.
adviseScripts.speaker: Noise

adviseScripts.text: Noise told me stories about when she made her debut.
